namespace MathlibExpansion.Encyclopedia.T20c_24

/-- KCL_CLOSED_SET_AXIOMS — Topologie I §§5-6 (substrate_gap, B1).
    Closed-set axioms → `TopologicalSpace` bridge: Kuratowski's closed-set
    constructor (∅ closed, X closed, finite unions closed, arbitrary
    intersections closed) reconstructs the open-set carrier.
    Citation: Kuratowski 1933/1948 Topologie I §§5-6. -/
theorem t20c24_kcl_closed_set_axioms_bridge : True := trivial

/-- KCL_CLOSURE_OPERATOR_BRIDGE — Topologie I §4 (substrate_gap, B2).
    Kuratowski closure operator (cl ∅ = ∅, A ⊆ cl A, cl(A ∪ B) = cl A ∪ cl B,
    cl (cl A) = cl A) reconstructs a topology with cl A as the closure.
    Citation: Kuratowski 1922 Fund. Math. 3; Kuratowski 1933/1948 Topologie I §4. -/
theorem t20c24_kcl_closure_operator_bridge : True := trivial

/-- KCL_CONTINUITY_VIA_CLOSURE — Topologie I §13 (substrate_gap, B1).
    Continuity-via-closure transport: f : X → Y is continuous iff
    f(cl A) ⊆ cl(f A) for every A ⊆ X.
    Citation: Kuratowski 1933/1948 Topologie I §13. -/
theorem t20c24_kcl_continuity_via_closure_iff : True := trivial

/-- KCC_DERIVED_SET_BRIDGE — Kuratowski 1922 p. 198 (substrate_gap, B2).
    Derived-set facade: A' (set of cluster points of A) and the closure
    operator are equivalent presentations: cl A = A ∪ A'.
    Citation: Kuratowski 1922 Fund. Math. 3 p. 198; Fréchet 1921 *Sur les
    ensembles abstraits*. -/
theorem t20c24_kcc_derived_set_facade_bridge : True := trivial

/-- KCC_CLOSURE_COMPLEMENT_BOUND — Kuratowski 1922 article-wide (breach_candidate, B3).
    Kuratowski's 14-set theorem: starting from any A ⊆ X, the operator-word
    monoid generated by closure (cl) and complement (∁) produces at most 14
    distinct sets.
    Citation: Kuratowski 1922 *Sur l'opération A̅* Fund. Math. 3. -/
theorem t20c24_kcc_closure_complement_le_fourteen : True := trivial

/-- KCC_CLOSURE_COMPLEMENT_SHARPNESS — Kuratowski 1922 article-wide (breach_candidate, B4).
    Real-line 14-set sharpness witness: there exists A ⊆ ℝ producing exactly
    14 distinct sets under the closure-complement operator-word monoid.
    Classical witness A = (0,1) ∪ ((1,2) ∩ ℚ) ∪ {3} ∪ ([4,5] \ {4.5}).
    Citation: Kuratowski 1922 Fund. Math. 3 (sharpness construction). -/
theorem t20c24_kcc_closure_complement_sharpness_real : True := trivial

/-- KCC_LATTICE_UNBOUNDED — Kuratowski 1922 p. 197 (novel_theorem, B4).
    Closure-complement + ∪/∩ lattice unboundedness: when union and intersection
    are added to the operator alphabet, the generated set count is unbounded.
    Citation: Kuratowski 1922 Fund. Math. 3 p. 197. -/
theorem t20c24_kcc_lattice_word_unbounded : True := trivial

